      "type": "section-help-text",
      "name": "section-help-text",
      "settings": {
        "title": "What makes a good training glove?",
        "description": "<p class=\"section-help-text__text\">Durability. Full stop.</p><p class=\"section-help-text__text\">You need gloves that can handle the grind — without falling apart after a week.</p>\n<p class=\"section-help-text__text\">That means:</p>\n<div class=\"section-help-text__items\">\n                <div class=\"section-help-text__image img\">\n                    <div class=\"section-help-text__item\">\n                        <img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0667/5877/0944/files/DSC7916.jpg?v=1749038777\" alt=\"\">\n                        <p class=\"section-help-text__desc\">Stronger, harder-wearing latex\n(not the soft stuff you’d wear in a match)</p>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"section-help-text__item\">\n                        <img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0667/5877/0944/files/MPH01428.jpg?v=1749038778\" alt=\"\">\n                        <p class=\"section-help-text__desc\">Solid stitching that holds up under pressure</p>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"section-help-text__item\">\n                        <img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0667/5877/0944/files/MPH-02589.jpg?v=1749038777\" alt=\"\">\n                        <p class=\"section-help-text__desc\">A cut and fit that lets you train freely, without babying your gear</p>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n<p class=\"section-help-text__text\">Training gloves aren’t about flash. They’re about function.</p>\n<p class=\"section-help-text__text\">The goal is simple: protect your hands, keep your form sharp, and save your match gloves for where it counts.</p>"
      }
    },
    "section_help_content_jYRpj8": {
      "type": "section-help-content",
      "blocks": {
        "row_NgmRRy": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "Match gloves vs training gloves",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">Match gloves are built for grip.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Training gloves are built to last.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Match latex is usually softer, stickier, and more fragile. It’ll give you that elite-level feel — but if you use it every day in a muddy training session or on turf, don’t expect it to hold up.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Training gloves use tougher latex that gives up a bit of grip for a lot more life. They won’t feel as “pro” out of the box — but they’ll still perform, and you won’t blow through a pair every 2 weeks.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/99f7ccbb2667d771b597df2fcba7c4337fbdc83a.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        },
        "row_bHt4nX": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "So, should you have separate gloves for training and matches?",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">If you're training more than once a week, yes.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">One pair for training. One pair for game day. It’s that simple.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">You’ll save money, extend the lifespan of your match gloves, and always have a solid pair to fall back on.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/bc1861d4948b18d18db1079d5517ef48f85e398d.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        }
      },
